The Telegraph - Calcutta
 CAB secretary to visit Lahore
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Following a circular from the BCCI, one representative from each of its affiliated units has been asked to visit Pakistan to watch a Test match of their choice. The CAB has nominated its joint-secretary Bablu Kolay, who will watch the second Test beginning in Lahore on April 5. It has been learnt that Kolay himself has expressed his wish to see the Lahore Test. He leaves on April 4. Samiran Chakraborty of Tripura will also be making the trip. It was also learnt that some representatives from the affiliated units are already there for the ODIs, some of whom will return once the ODI series gets over.  Copyright 
